OL,3,CAmbulance workers vote to strike in
OL,4,Cresponse to proposed new shift system
OL,6,FUnite the union represents more than
OL,7,F400 paramedics and ambulance workers
OL,8,Femployed by the NI Ambulance Service.
OL,10,FThis comes after the release of a
OL,11,Fdamning report on the ambulance
OL,12,Fhandover times in Northern Ireland.
OL,14,FWithin the findings, it was revealed
OL,15,Fthe number of handovers taking more
OL,16,Fthan three hours rose from around 400
OL,17,F(less than 1%) in 2019/20 to just over
OL,18,F11,000 (9%) in 2023/24.
